Create an empty list called my_list.
Append the following elements to my_list: 10, 20, 30, 40.
Insert the value 15 at the second position in the list.
Extend my_list with another list: [50, 60, 70].
Remove the last element from my_list.
Sort my_list in ascending order.
Find and print the index of the value 30 in my_list.

mylist = []
mylist.append(10)
mylist.append(20)
mylist.append(30)
mylist.append(40)

print(f"the appended list contains : {mylist}")

#inseting the value 15 at the second position
mylist.insert(1,15)
print(f"the new list after inserting 15 is :{mylist}")

#extend my list with another list
thislist = [50,60,70]
mylist.extend(thislist)
print(f"the new list after extending thislist is: {mylist}")

#removing the last item  from the list
mylist.pop()
print(f"my list after removing the last item in the list is: {mylist}")

#sorting my list in ascendind order
mylist.sort()
print(f"new list after sorting is : {mylist}")

#finding and printing the index of the value 30 in  my list
print(f"the index of 30 is : {mylist.index(30)}")
